cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of sentiment classification, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP. The paper also discusses the use of naive Bayesian (NB) classification, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses experimental results to evaluate the proposed method, which suggests the involvement of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) subcategories.
